subject: p10975446
Findings: The ET tube is still slightly low, 17 cm above the carina. Right IJ line tip is at the cavoatrial junction. There are bilateral pleural effusions, vascular plethora, patchy areas of alveolar edema. The overall impression is that of CHF and underlying infectious infiltrate cannot be excluded. Compared to the prior study, the fluid status is slightly worse.
